==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Kerite
<hw>Ke"rite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>ke`ras</grk>, horn.]</ety> <def>A compound in which tar or
asphaltum combined with animal or vegetable oils is vulcanized by
sulphur, the product closely resembling rubber; -- used principally as
an insulating material in telegraphy.</def>
<rj><au>Knight.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

